  "prompt": "What are the questions asked in interviews?",
  "response": "Interview questions can vary widely depending on the role, industry, and company. However, there are several common categories and specific questions that are frequently asked in interviews. Here are some typical types and examples of interview questions:\n\n### General Background Questions\n1. **Tell me about yourself.**\n2. **What motivated you to apply for this position?**\n3. **What do you know about our company?**\n4. **What are your greatest strengths and weaknesses?**\n\n### Behavioral Questions\n1. **Describe a challenging situation you faced at work and how you handled it.**\n2. **Give an example of a time you worked in a team. What was your role?**\n3. **Tell me about a time you had to meet a tight deadline. How did you manage it?**\n4. **Can you describe a conflict you had with a coworker and how you resolved it?**\n\n### Situational Questions\n1. **What would you do if you were given a project with a very tight deadline?**\n2. **How would you handle a situation where a team member is not contributing?**\n3. **If a client is unhappy with your work, how would you address their concerns?**\n\n### Technical/Job-Specific Questions\n1. **What programming languages are you proficient in?** (for tech roles)\n2. **How do you stay updated with industry trends and developments?**\n3. **Can you explain [specific technical concept or process]?**\n4. **What tools or software are you familiar with that will help you in this role?**\n\n### Questions About Goals and Motivation\n1. **Where do you see yourself in five years?**\n2. **What are your career goals?**\n3. **What do you hope to achieve in this role?**\n\n### Company Culture and Fit\n1. **What makes a successful team member in your view?**\n2. **How do you prioritize your work?**\n3. **Describe your ideal work environment.**\n\n### Questions for You to Ask\n1. **What does a typical day look like for this position?**\n2. **What are the biggest challenges the team is currently facing?**\n3. **How do you measure success in this role?**\n4. **What opportunities are there for professional development in this company?**\n\n### Closing Questions\n1. **Do you have any questions for us?**\n2. **Is there anything else you would like to add that we haven\u2019t covered?**\n\nIt's essential to prepare for a range of questions and to have thoughtful answers ready, as well as questions to ask the interviewer to demonstrate your interest in the role and organization.",
